{"name": "pyerf", "metadata": {"name": "pyerf", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 or later (GPLv3+)", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Mathematics"], "home_page": "https://www.github.com/dougthor42/pyerf", "license": "GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A pure-Python implementation of the error function and inverse error function.", "upload_time": 1498166503}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  docs: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-pythonhosted-brightgreen.svg\n    :alt: Documentation Status\n    :target: https://pythonhosted.org/pyerf\n    ```\n  pypi: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pyerf.svg\n    :alt: Latest PyPI version\n    :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyerf/\n    ```\n  pythonversion: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/pyerf.svg\n    :alt: Supported Python Versions\n    :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyerf/\n    ```\n  travis: |-\n    ```{image} https://travis-ci.org/dougthor42/PyErf.svg?branch=master\n    :alt: Travis-CI (Linux, Max)\n    :target: https://travis-ci.org/dougthor42/PyErf\n    ```\n  wheels: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/wheel/pyerf.svg\n    :alt: Python Wheels\n    :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyerf/\n    ```\n---\n\n# PyErf\n\n## A Pure-Python Error Function and Inverse Error Function Package\n\n{{ travis }} {{ pypi }} {{ wheels }} {{ pythonversion }} {{ docs }}\n\n`pyerf` is a pure-Python implementation of the error function and\ninverse error function using the same functions that [SciPy] uses (namely\nparts of the Cephes math library, [cprob/ndtr.c] and [cprob/ndtri.c]).\n\nThis is a useful package for when you need to calculate some error fuctions\nbut you don't want to install all of the [SciPy]/[NumPy] stuff.\n\n## Usage\n\nYou can import the module:\n\n```python\nfrom pyerf import pyerf\npyerf.erfinv(0.5)         # 0.476936...\npyerf.erf(0.5)            # 0.5204998...\npyerf.erfc(0.5)           # 0.4795001...\n```\n\nor the package:\n\n```python\nimport pyerf\npyerf.erfinv(0.5)         # 0.476936...\npyerf.erf(0.5)            # 0.5204998...\npyerf.erfc(0.5)           # 0.4795001...\n```\n\nor only a specific function:\n\n```python\nfrom pyerf import erfinv as inverse_error_function\ninverse_error_function(0.5)       # 0.476936...\n```\n\nand lastly, you can even use `import *` (but that's no longer considered\nvery Pythonic as it pollutes the namespace):\n\n```python\nfrom pyerf import *\nerfinv(0.5)         # 0.476936...\nerf(0.5)            # 0.5204998...\nerfc(0.5)           # 0.4795001...\n```\n\n## Changelog\n\nSee [CHANGELOG.md].\n\n% Images and Links\n\n[changelog.md]: https://github.com/dougthor42/PyErf/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md\n[cprob/ndtr.c]: https://github.com/jeremybarnes/cephes/blob/master/cprob/ndtr.c\n[cprob/ndtri.c]: https://github.com/jeremybarnes/cephes/blob/master/cprob/ndtri.c\n[numpy]: http://www.numpy.org/\n[scipy]: https://www.scipy.org/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pyerf.tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyerf", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pyerf.erf", "xref": {"fqname": "pyerf.pyerf.erf", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyerf.erfc", "xref": {"fqname": "pyerf.pyerf.erfc", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyerf.erfinv", "xref": {"fqname": "pyerf.pyerf.erfinv", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pyerf.__about__", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"n