yerf._ndtri", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "y", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Port of cephes `ndtri.c`: inverse normal distribution function.\n\nSee <https://github.com/jeremybarnes/cephes/blob/master/cprob/ndtri.c>\n"]}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.erfinv", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "z", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calculate the inverse error function at point `z`.\n\nThis is a direct port of the SciPy `erfinv` function, originally\nwritten in C.\n\n# Parameters\n\nz : numeric\n\n# Returns\n\nfloat\n\n# References\n\n- <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Error_function#Inverse_functions>\n- <http://functions.wolfram.com/GammaBetaErf/InverseErf/>\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> round(erfinv(0.1), 12)\n0.088855990494\n>>> round(erfinv(0.5), 12)\n0.476936276204\n>>> round(erfinv(-0.5), 12)\n-0.476936276204\n>>> round(erfinv(0.95), 12)\n1.38590382435\n>>> round(erf(erfinv(0.3)), 3)\n0.3\n>>> round(erfinv(erf(0.5)), 3)\n0.5\n>>> erfinv(0)\n0\n>>> erfinv(1)\ninf\n>>> erfinv(-1)\n-inf\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "pyerf.pyerf.PI", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.ROOT_2PI", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.EXP_NEG2", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.inf", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.MAXVAL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.erf", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.erfc", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.erf", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyerf.pyerf.erfc", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}